@node history " History "
@toc information



 @{b}The History@{ub}


 Version : V1.0 (1/1 in 1995)
 Released: 11th November 1995 (Amiga Exposition `95)
 Size    : 336.516K
 Comment : the first public release

 Version : 1/3 in 1996
 Released: 24th January 1996
 Size    : 483.731K
 Numbers : informationon about 143 parties and 1158 productions
 Comment : improved the lay-out a lot, especially the overview
           of the parties (main-table); included an index part
           (thanks to Ralph Seichter for his Agix V1.2);  cor-
           rected some mistakes and  cleaned up  some trouble-
           making links; added an install-script, Read-Me-Text
           and a few nice icons and, of course, added much in-
           formation about new and old productions & parties!

 Version : 2/3 in 1996
 Released: 19th April 1996
 Size    : 519 Kb
 Numbers : informationon about 173 parties and 1263 productions
 Comment : improved the lay-out a little bit more; included two
           nice sound-modules and a beautiful title-picture,...




 @{b}The Future@{ub}

  The  guide  will be updated about every 4th month, so there will
  be  3  issues  in  a  year,  one  in January (after The Party in
  Denmark),  one  in  May  (after The Gathering) and one in August
  after the big parties (see the calendar for the exact dates).

  I have  much more texts  which will be  used in  this guide,  so
  expect The Scene to  grow a lot in the future  (this  depends on
  your support too!). Then again, more information will be pressed
  into  each party, like visitors, prices, extra events and so on.
  Plus I want to add the party  where a production was released to
  each of its description  (if you click from index you don`t know
  exactly when it was released) ... and I have a lot more ideas.

  As soon as possible  we will include  a short description of the
  productions  (e.g. what happens in the demo, what music-style is
  offered in the sounddisk, etc.) ... be surprised or be dead! :-b

  I have seen 2 guide-viewers  in the near past,  but one was ugly
  and the other did not display  this guide correctly,  reason un-
  known.  Could someone please send me a nice guide-viewer??

  I would like someone to create a nice  installer-script  for the
  original Commodore Installer and probably someone who could code
  a small intro for @{i}The Scene.@{ui}
@endnode

